ce:section.ce:para:
The research found that the RWC of apricot seedlings decreased when they were subjected to water deficit (Table 2
                        ). However, the application of Cys, GQDs, and Cys-GQD NPs through the leaves improved their RWC under normal as well as water deficit conditions. Drought stress caused a reduction of 21.22% in the RWC of the apricot plant as compared to the control plant. The maximum significant diminution in relative water content was achieved when the soil moisture level was at 25% FC, without foliar application. However, the foliar application of Cys, GQDs, and Cys-GQD NPs increased the relative water content of the plant at all levels of drought stress (Fig. 3
                        a).

According to the study, when apricot plants are exposed to drought stress, spraying them with a nanocomposite of Cys, GQDS, and Cys-GQDs NPs can significantly impact their enzymatic activity. Specifically, the APX, GPX, and SOD enzymes are affected, as well as the plants' total antioxidant capacity (Table 4
                        ). The Cys-GQDs NPs nanocomposite treatment resulted in the highest APX activity, while the control plants showed the lowest data. Compared to the control apricot plants, the ones treated with Cys-GQDs NPs nanocomposite exhibited 40.15% more APX activity. Furthermore, drought stress led to a 1.54-fold increase in APX activity over the control apricot plants (Fig. 7
                        b and c). The plants treated with Cys-GQDs NPs and 25% FC exhibited the highest SOD activity, while the control plants had the lowest. Foliar treatment with Cys-GQDs NPs in FC25% resulted in a 132.73% increase in SOD activity over to the control apricot plants (Fig. 7e). According to these findings when Cys, GQDs, and Cys-GQDs NPs are applied to the leaves, they improve GPX activity by 72.43%, 14.54%, and 15.38%, in conditions of 100%, 50%, and 25% field capacity, respectively. Under 25% FC and no foliar spraying, the activity improved by 6.5 times compared to the control plants. The activity of GPX was highest in 25% FC. Foliar application of Cys-GQDs NPs increased the activity by 93.33% compared to the control (Fig. 7d). The application of nanocomposites foliar spraying increased PPO activity by 60.27% under 100%, 50%, and 25% FC drought when compared to the control plants (Fig. 7f and g).
